    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-05-15T17:08:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-05-15T17:08:00-05:00" n="434"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.86231/5–1552: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>No. 434<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Certain Diplomatic and Consular Offices</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d434fn1">Sent to Tel Aviv, Jerusalem, Amman, Beirut,
                        Damascus, Paris, Ankara, Baghdad, Cairo, Jidda, New York, London, and
                        Tripoli.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-05-15T18:08:00-04:00"
                            >May 15, 1952—6:08 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>949. <persName corresp="#p_EAS1">Eban</persName> advises Israeli Govt prepared
                    release blocked accts Arab refugees and ready negot mechanics release with
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>, pursuant request made by Amb <persName
                        corresp="#p_PEE1">Palmer</persName> on behalf <gloss target="#t_PCC1"
                        >PCC</gloss> May 5. He stated amt involved equivalent approx $14 million and
                    Israel Govt prepared pay into some <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> acct $2.8
                    million with balance as needed. Amb said his govt hopes US will use its good
                    offices obtain release block Jewish bank accts in Iraq but Israel release not
                    conditioned on such action.</p>
                <p>If approached re above, statement shld be made this is voluntary Israel Govt
                    action, fol recent conversations between <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss> and
                    Israel Govt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
